# Testing Standards

## Test Commands

### Primary Commands

- **`pnpm test:run`** - Run all tests once and exit (recommended for development)
- **`pnpm test:ui`** - Interactive test UI for debugging
- **`pnpm test:coverage`** - Run tests with coverage report

### Optional Commands

- **`pnpm test`** - Watch mode (automatically re-runs tests on file changes)

## Recommended Workflow

### For Development

Use **`pnpm test:run`** for quick test verification:

- Faster execution
- Lower resource usage
- Clean exit after completion
- Ideal for pre-commit checks

### For Debugging

Use **`pnpm test:ui`** when you need to:

- Debug failing tests interactively
- Explore test results visually
- Run specific test files or cases
- Inspect component snapshots

### For CI/CD

Always use **`pnpm test:run`** in automated pipelines for reliable, single-pass execution

## Testing Stack

- **Vitest**: Fast unit test framework powered by Vite
- **React Testing Library**: User-centric testing utilities
- **Playwright**: E2E testing for browser automation
- **user-event**: Simulate user interactions
- **@testing-library/jest-dom**: Custom matchers for DOM testing

